                                <condition/>
                            </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout>No Ogham is present on the stone, but there is a roman-letter inscription in two lines reading vertically downwards. The inscription begins nearly halfway down the face of the stone and is, according to Edwards (2007, 219), <q>quite deeply incised</q>.</layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote><q>The inscription is in capitals... except for miniscule Q, which has an open loop. The A's have angle-bars and the I's at the ends of both lines are horizontal. In line 2 FI and LI are conjoined and the I's are of small size; the top horizontal of the F slopes upward and the bottom downward; L has a downward sloping horizontal; B has separate loops and R has an extended vertical... The combination of letter-forms... together with the post-syncope name forms, suggests the inscription is late in the series</q> (Edwards 2007, 219).                                
                                <height></height>
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>
                    </physDesc>
