                            <origDate notBefore="0550" notAfter="0600" precision="low" datingMethod="#julian" evidence="linguistic">Second half of the sixth century A.D.</origDate>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance type="found">Stone was first discovered by Lhuyd, but Macalister seems to be the first to suggest Ogham. Says in 1922 that he saw a line of ogham reflecting the Latin inscription, but that the second time he visited it had been disintegrated apart from a few hollows left over. McManus dismisses this as 'imaginary'.
